content:
Configure New Hire Enrollment and Termination Workflows for the Salesforce Data Model.

The Mid-term Adjustments Lightning web component gives insurance carrier administrators a straightforward way to terminate group census members individually or in bulk asynchronously and enroll new hires in the middle of a contract term asynchronously.

Add the Mid-Term Adjustments LWC to the Account Page

Input Parameters:

INPUT PROPERTY	PURPOSE
Bulk Termination CSV Template	The name of the template CSV file for bulk termination.
New Hire CSV Template	The name of the template CSV file for new hire enrollment.
Person Account Enabled	Specifies whether the user uses the Person Account flow for enrollment.

Set Up New Hire Enrollment CSV Template

Create a batch job to process new hire enrollment requests asynchronously.

Configure Salesforce Flow and OmniScript:

* Configure the Enrollment flow compiles available products for group census members and process bulk enrollment.
* Customize the OmniScript that walks users through uploading census data for Group Benefits new hire enrollments.
* Set up error handling to get notified if any errors occur during a CSV file upload and when completed asynchronous jobs identify missing or incomplete data

Configure FlexCard to Launch New Hire Enrollment OmniScript on Group Account Page.

Create Insurance Enrollment Batch Job for Asynchronous New Hire Enrollment, Configure Salesforce Flow for New Hire Enrollment, Configure OmniScript and Set Up Error Handling for New Hire Enrollment.
title: Configuring Mid-Term Adjustments for Salesforce
